2
00:00:15.546 --> 00:00:18.957
When Arnold Schoenberg and
others created atonal music,

3
00:00:18.957 --> 00:00:22.020
he also created a problem, as we've seen.

4
00:00:22.020 --> 00:00:26.930
With no guide or game plan for
musical structure, how to proceed?

5
00:00:26.930 --> 00:00:32.800
Well Schoenberg came up with a system, a
set of rules that gave structure to music.

6
00:00:32.800 --> 00:00:38.170
A kind of music called 12-tone
music because it uses,

7
00:00:38.170 --> 00:00:42.600
in sequence,
all 12 tones of the chromatic scale.

8
00:00:42.600 --> 00:00:48.840
It's also called serial music because
the 12 pitches come in a fixed series.

9
00:00:48.840 --> 00:00:50.900
Here's how the game is played.

10
00:00:52.110 --> 00:00:57.940
First, the composer can choose
any pleasing sequence of pitches,

11
00:00:57.940 --> 00:01:02.660
but all 12 pitches, all chromatic notes
within the octave have to be used, and

12
00:01:02.660 --> 00:01:06.970
have to come in a series,
or in a sequence of 12.

13
00:01:06.970 --> 00:01:09.430
This is called the row.

14
00:01:09.430 --> 00:01:11.730
The row many start on any pitch.

15
00:01:11.730 --> 00:01:16.740
You could start on C, or E, or
F sharp, or B flat, whatever.

16
00:01:18.062 --> 00:01:21.030
The pitches in the row may
sound vertically as a chord.

17
00:01:21.030 --> 00:01:24.140
You could have one, two,
three come in succession, or one, two,

18
00:01:24.140 --> 00:01:27.240
three sound simultaneously.

19
00:01:27.240 --> 00:01:29.250
The rows may overlap.

20
00:01:29.250 --> 00:01:31.180
The row may go backward.

21
00:01:31.180 --> 00:01:32.750
We call that retrograde motion.

22
00:01:32.750 --> 00:01:37.500
The row may go upside down,
be inverted, or an exact mirror image.

23
00:01:37.500 --> 00:01:39.190
That's called inversion.

24
00:01:39.190 --> 00:01:44.300
The row may go upside down and
backward, retrograde inversion.

25
00:01:44.300 --> 00:01:48.090
And finally, the composer can
use any meters and rhythms.

26
00:01:48.090 --> 00:01:52.720
Rhythm is not a primary issue here.

27
00:01:53.880 --> 00:01:57.420
Well, as they say, a picture is worth
a thousand words, and if that's true,

28
00:01:57.420 --> 00:01:59.250
maybe a video is worth a 100,000.

29
