Obviously, that's what all the one, two,
three, fours, and so on, are about.

89
00:06:01.030 --> 00:06:06.000
In the boxes, you can see all the various
permutations that Schoenberg applies,

90
00:06:06.000 --> 00:06:10.410
retrograde, inversion,
retrograde-inversion, and so on.

91
00:06:10.410 --> 00:06:14.940
And remember that the row can start
on any pitch within the octave.

92
00:06:14.940 --> 00:06:20.290
